HB 428 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Bayham
Abstract: Creates the "2023 and 2025 LSU Fighting Tigers College World Series
Champions" special prestige license plate and provides for the creation, issuance,
design, consent, implementation, fees, distributions, and promulgation of rules
applicable to this license plate.
Proposed law requires that the Dept. of Public Safety and Corrections (DPS&C), office of
motor vehicles (OMV), issue a special prestige license plate to be known as the "2023 and
2025 LSU Fighting Tigers College World Series Champions" license plate, provided that
there is a minimum of 1,000 applicants for such plates.
Proposed law specifies that the plate is restricted to use on passenger cars, pickup trucks,
recreational vehicles, motorcycles, and vans. Further specifies that application for a special
prestige license plate under proposed law constitutes prior written consent and instruction
by the applicant to the dept. to provide his personal identifying information to La. State
University. Further requires the DPS&C, OMV, to create this special prestige license plate
when the applicable statutory provisions are met and the department's electronic vehicle and
registration system is updated to accommodate the creation of the new plates.
Proposed law requires the secretary work in conjunction with the LSU Bd. of Supervisors
to select the color and design of the plate. Requires the design include the words "2023 and
2025 LSU Fighting Tigers College World Series Champions".
Proposed law specifies that the plate will be issued, upon application, to any citizen of the
state in the same manner as any other motor vehicle license plate.
Proposed law requires that the dept. collect an annual royalty fee of $25 in addition to the
standard motor vehicle license tax imposed in present law and a handling fee of $3.50 for
each plate to be retained by the dept. to offset a portion of administrative costs.
Proposed law requires the department collect an annual royalty fee and forward it to LSU
as a charitable donation to the school by the applicant. Further specifies that the monies
received by LSU can only be used for academic or financial need-based scholarships.
Proposed law specifies that after the signing of a contract that authorizes the use of the LSU
logo, the secretary of DPS&C must establish the "2023 and 2025 LSU Fighting Tigers
College World Series Champions" license plate in accordance with proposed law.
Proposed law requires the secretary promulgate and adopt rules and regulations as necessary
to implement the provisions of proposed law.
(Adds R.S. 47:463.243)
